# The undefined-risk cousin of the condor: no wings, more credit, and a
# loss stop doing the work the wings would. PRIOR's explain output says
# "undefined risk until closed" for a reason — the [loss 200%] line is
# not optional equipment on this one.

strategy "Quiet Tape Strangle"

universe $SPY

when [quiet 1.5%]
  write [strangle delta=15 dte=45]

close at [profit 50%]
  or [loss 200%]
  or [dte 10]

risk [contracts 1]
